Seasons change 🍁
#weroamgermany #fall #autumn #germany

Evening in Lysefjord - while I was sitting on the edge of a 1000m cliff I watched the sun turning this waterfall into a golden river - what an unreal sight!
That was first night out in the Fjords during my last summer trip to Norway, guess it could not have started any better 🤗
#norway#norge#lysefjorden#midnightsun#arcticsummer

A quiet morning up in the Arctic 🇳🇴
We camped next to the shore on a small gravel road that night. With beautiful sunset light we went to bed woke up during the night and saw a double rainbow with the midnight sun. Eventually the next morning it looked like this - Norway is full of surprises 😍
#norway #norge #nordkapp #arcticsummer #midnightsun #fisherboat

A hygge late summer evening in Northern Germany. Did you ever hear of the word hygge? It comes from the Danish and is used to describe a moment, whether alone or with friends, as cosy, charming or special. For me that was exactly this moment - with our feet in the lake and a cold beer we watched the swans circling some last rounds on the lake before the sun set behind the trees.
Now I'm giving you the chance to win this backpack for your own hygge moment! 🎒 Be in the draw by simply commenting why you should win it & follow @carlsberg_de and my account. Good luck ✌️
#probably #carlsberg #rightbeerrightnow #theDanishWay #hygge
A morning well spent 🇦🇹 #stayandwander #weroamabroad #salzkammergut #austria #österreich

Enjoying the views high above Plansee - thanks for the behind the scenes shot @asasteinars 🙂
#stayandwander#plansee#austria

Early morning missions at home - just a 30 Minute drive from my place this beautiful castle is situated perfectly on top of a hill, towering above the town for almost 800 years. Crazy to think what they were able to build things like this at this time 😍
Shot on a @djiglobal #Mavic2Pro
#SeeTheBiggerPicture
#weroamgermany

From a beautiful autumns day in the Berchtesgaden Alps - enjoying one of the last warm days on Obersee Lake with @tashi_ka 🍁
Now it feels like autumn came to an end, but I’m also getting excited for winter to come - what are you plans for the season? 🤗 ❄️ #weroamgermany #weroamhome #stayandwander #germany #berchtesgaden #königssee #sharegermany

From a pitch black night somewhere far beyond the Arctic Circle in Norway. -25°C, probably 20 layers and just waiting for something to happen. And then out of nowhere the beams started coming down the sky, perfectly aligning with the Mountain of Stetind - the most artistic Aurora I have ever seen!
Can’t wait for these days to come again 🙌
#norge #aurora #narvik #mittfriluftsliv #northernlights

An evenings dream in the Arctic 🏄 We spent it sitting on the shore watching those guys practice in the waves and while they weren’t able to get up on their boards, they had their time of their life as far as we could hear from their laughter. ,The best surfer out there is the one having the most fun’ 🙌
#norway#norge#arcticsurf#kvalvika#lofoten#reine#stayandwander#unstadarcticsurf

Solitude - it’s always important to find your quiet place. On this spot I’m sitting just a few kilometers away from one of the worlds most famous treks - the hike to Trolltunga. While crowds are lining up to do their poses on the tip of the tongue during the day I tried to find a place to enjoy this beautiful view how it should be - in absolute silence ✌️
#norge #preikestolen #norway #mittfriluftsliv

From a summer in the Faroe Islands 🇫🇴
I still can’t get over the dramatic landscape there. Especially in summer, when the grass is so green that you need to desaturate it in post, the rugged coastline stands out even more in contrast to the calm & soft ocean. I have to go back soon again 😍
#faroeislands#visitfaroeislands#føroyar#faroes#kalsoy#torshavn#arcticsummer

Solitude at Preikestolen - a rare thing since it’s usually crowded with people shortly after sunset. No idea why but this day was different - that’s also what this stranger probably thought while he cheered loudly on the edge 😀

location.location_name: Homberg An Der Ohm, Hessen, Germany

list.comment:
Last Friday I met with @lennart and @hannes_becker to start a series of #WeRoamHome where we try to encourage people to explore their local backyard. Not always you need to travel far to find beauty, sometimes beauty lies around you and the most simple things turn out to be really gorgeous. For example this shot I took when we explored Hannes’ backyard that morning. We came across a small forest with sun rays shining through and together with the last morning fog, it created something really magical. Have you ever tried to explore your home? If so, feel free use the hashtag 🤗
#WeRoamGermany #Homberg #Hessen #Stayandwander

High above Lysefjord - trying to get a glimpse of the drop 🇳🇴
#midnightsun #mittfriluftsliv #norge #preikestolen #norway
